I want to create a simple diagram that can help people determine how to facilitate sessions that promote post traumatic growth - the theory is that to encourage PTG we need to increase mental flexibility with deliberate rumination questions and synergistically connected to community and connection - something that can be connected by coming together in a safe space to discuss which connects to the framing I'm trying to place things into. I believe that polyvagal theory can connect to post traumatic growth as an organizing framework - you can either decrease stress or increase competence (which also decreases stress) to prevent people from freezing in the face of traumatic events and learning to construct a new narrative when the current organizing worldview is falling apart. which leads to the new possibilities, deeper relationships, greater appreciation for life, spiritual development, and personal strength

Act as a researcher reviewing PTG literature, resilience literature, as well as polyvagal theory and come up with a polyvagal theory and framework and 3 diagrams we can use to explain factors that lead to post traumatic growth and can help people design new pedagogies that include those factors into their training programs as a structure to promote PTG while transferring knowledge
